cosmicsnip (1.0.0-1) noble; urgency=medium

  * First stable release.
  * Libadwaita UI — HeaderBar, ToolbarView, ToastOverlay.
  * System tray icon via DBus StatusNotifierItem (COSMIC panel bar).
  * App stays alive between snips — re-activate from dock or tray.
  * Out-of-bounds annotation: canvas scales to fit with 25% margin,
    annotations can extend past the screenshot edge.
  * Copy/save renders as transparent PNG, auto-trimmed to content bounds.
  * Multi-monitor layer-shell overlays with shared selection state.
  * Ctrl+N for new snip, Ctrl+Q to quit, Esc to close editor.

 -- itssoup <itssoup@users.noreply.github.com>  Sun, 16 Mar 2026 22:00:00 +0000

cosmicsnip (0.2.0-1) noble; urgency=medium

  * Multi-monitor support via wlr-layer-shell (per-monitor native overlays)
  * Monitor config file at ~/.config/cosmicsnip/monitors.json
  * App icon (soupfi_icon_dark.svg) installed to hicolor icon theme
  * Editor toolbar migrated to Gtk.HeaderBar
  * Updated CSS to match COSMIC dark glass aesthetic
  * CRITICAL: Fixed TOCTOU race condition in temp file chmod
  * Removed dead wl-copy clipboard code (now uses GTK4 native clipboard)
  * Added PIL decompression bomb limit
  * Hardened log file permissions (0600)
  * Added temp directory ownership verification
  * Added save path validation (blocks writes to system directories)
  * Sanitized XDG environment variable paths
  * Hardened notification subprocess (truncation + timeout)
  * Added per-stroke point cap (10000 points)
  * Set process umask 0077 at startup

 -- itssoup <itssoup@users.noreply.github.com>  Sun, 16 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000

cosmicsnip (0.1.0-1) noble; urgency=low

  * Initial release.
  * Core capture via cosmic-screenshot (XDG Desktop Portal).
  * Drag-to-select region overlay with multi-monitor support.
  * Annotation editor: pen, highlighter, arrow, rectangle tools.
  * GTK4 native Wayland clipboard (no wl-copy subprocess blocking).
  * Save As dialog with full path control.
  * Security hardening: no root execution, symlink checks, path validation.

